{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-post-template-js","path":"/step-four-to-react-routing-with-react-router","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"blurb":"Frontend Engineer @ LaunchDarkly. Book addict and tea lover. Passionate about react graphql and making things simple and fast."}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I am in LA for holidays! Yep, I'm blogging as I am holidaying; I don't know why but I just can't stop thinking about it.\nMy wife says I'm addicted to work, I said no. We fight a lot but we love each other. Love is weird.</p>\n<p>Anyway! This is a short and basic guide to implement routing with react router.\nIf you haven't read my <a href=\"/step-three-to-react-speed-dev-with-hot-module-replacement/\">previous post</a>,\nit might be a good idea to have a quick read before reading this one. We'll build this example based on that last post.\nLet's get into it!</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-41-install-react-router\"><a href=\"#step-41-install-react-router\" aria-label=\"step 41 install react router permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4.1: Install react-router</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> --save react-router</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>The latest version of react-router at the time of writing is 2.5.1. This single npm package is sufficient for\nall our routing needs.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-42-initialise-routes\"><a href=\"#step-42-initialise-routes\" aria-label=\"step 42 initialise routes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4.2: Initialise routes</h2>\n<p>You set up react router routes in jsx. What does that mean? That means you set up your routes\nthe same way you write jsx; in an xml-like format with nested parent-child structure. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jsx line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Route<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> IndexRoute<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-router'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> App <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./component/appComponent'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Home <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./component/homeComponent'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Contact <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./component/contactComponent'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> routes <span class=\"token operator\">=</span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Route</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">path</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">component</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>App<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n    </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">IndexRoute</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">component</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Home<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n    </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Route</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">path</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/contact<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">component</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Contact<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n  </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Route</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> routes<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Setting up routes like this maybe confusing to someone who is new to react router and perhaps even more confusing\nfor .NET developers who are used to setting up MVC routes. Let me explain how this works in react router:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Each \"Route\" element must specify a path and a component attribute.</li>\n<li>Incoming urls will be matched to a path. When matched, the corresponding component will be rendered.</li>\n<li>The previous point means that a path like \"/contact\" is actually a nested path which \nmatches <b>two</b> components at \"/\" and \"/contact\". That means <b>both</b> the App and Contact components will be rendered.\n</li>\n<li>IndexRoute is the default component which gets rendered when no nested route is specified i.e. when only \"/\" or \"\" is specified.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-43-add-react-router-links\"><a href=\"#step-43-add-react-router-links\" aria-label=\"step 43 add react router links permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4.3: Add react router links</h2>\n<p>You need to use the Link component from react-router package instead of the standard html anchor tags to\nbe able to route across pages SPA style.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jsx line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Link</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">to</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">Home</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Link</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Link</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">to</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/contact<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">Contact Us</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Link</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Each Link component needs to have a \"to\" attribute specified. The value of each \"to\" attribute must match a route specified in the route.js\nfile in the previous section.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-44-reactdom-render-router\"><a href=\"#step-44-reactdom-render-router\" aria-label=\"step 44 reactdom render router permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4.4: ReactDom render Router</h2>\n<p>Instead of rendering your root component directly on the client side, you render the Router component (from react-router package) with the routes attribute\nspecified. This is so we can match urls and render matching components using the routes declared in common/route.js\nThe history attribute tells react router to use html5 history api as opposed to hash history. If you don't specify this attribute,\nyou will get this warning: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>react-router<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">`</span>Router<span class=\"token variable\">`</span></span> no longer defaults the <span class=\"token function\">history</span> prop to \n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">hash</span> history. Please use the <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">`</span>hashHistory<span class=\"token variable\">`</span></span> singleton instead.\"</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Html5 history api is preferable to hash history because it keeps the url clean:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-html line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-html\">/contact</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>as opposed to:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-html line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-html\">/#/contact</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>The whole client/index.js looks like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jsx line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Import the render method from react-dom so we can mount our</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// component onto an html element</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>render<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-dom'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Router<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> browserHistory<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-router'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> routes <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'../common/route'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/**\n * Render the Router component with routes attribute so we can match urls \n * and render matching components using the routes declared in common/route.js.\n * The history attribute tells react router to use html5 history api as \n * opposed to hash history. Html5 history api is preferable to hash history \n * because it keeps the url clean e.g. \"/contact\" as opposed to \"/#/contact\"\n */</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Router</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">routes</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>routes<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">history</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token script-punctuation punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>browserHistory<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'reactDiv'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-45-write-child-react-components\"><a href=\"#step-45-write-child-react-components\" aria-label=\"step 45 write child react components permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 4.5: Write child React components!</h2>\n<p>Almost there! Now we create the actual Home and Contact components that\nget rendered when matched. These are pretty simple:</p>\n<h4 id=\"homecomponentjs\"><a href=\"#homecomponentjs\" aria-label=\"homecomponentjs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>homeComponent.js</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jsx line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Component<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Home</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">React junkie will rock ndc 2016 in Sydney!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"contactcomponentjs\"><a href=\"#contactcomponentjs\" aria-label=\"contactcomponentjs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>contactComponent.js</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jsx line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Component<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Contact</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">Contact us! 555-6969</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"step-46-some-finishing-touches-on-styling-and-run-the-app\"><a href=\"#step-46-some-finishing-touches-on-styling-and-run-the-app\" aria-label=\"step 46 some finishing touches on styling and run the app permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4